ENTRY       EC 3.4.22.47                Enzyme
NAME        gingipain K;
            Lys-gingipain;
            PrtP proteinase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Cysteine endopeptidases
REACTION    Endopeptidase with strict specificity for lysyl bonds
COMMENT     Activity is stimulated by glycine. Known from the bacterium Porphyromonas gingivalis and contributes to the pathogenicity of the organism. In peptidase family C25.
